<br>
Finished my 8th shawl a couple days ago.  Went to help a friend camp WW for furs today and there are no velium hounds up.  I've heard varying reports on what are PHes for the hounds (including only CoV faction mobs).  I did this part of the camp first.  Velium Hounds are soloable (epic, BoB, YMMV) and hit 150ish but low hp.  I had a druid bot to track them with when I went there, but this was the day before and the day that the 8th shawl patch was implemented.  I would say about 1 in4/5 drop on the furs.  If you have a ranger friend, they have a lot better time with the hounds than we do and a guild ranger camped most of the furs for me.  I should note that when I was soloing there, I died 3 time due to roaming adds (always velium hounds).  Please, someone tell me where that root earring drops in CT <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .  If you are KoS to CoV, this will be an evil camp for you (most mages on my server at least are +CoV due to needing to CoH in ToV).<br>
<br>
Blocks of velium are incredibly easy.  You can get them while exping in Velk's (got half that way) or you can get them in CC.  They drop off orcs in CC.  Relatively rare, but mages can just about clear every orc in the place before a respawn if you know your way around.  Also, if you can vend in Frostone (or whatever the city is called in there), they are usually loaded up with the blocks.  Sneak classes or chanter can make this happen.<br>
<br>
